%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thestreet.com%2Finvesting%2Fblackstone-ceo-argues-weve-seen-cyclical-bottom-for-firm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eearnings%20call%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20January.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Blackstone%20signage%20outside%20Blackstone%20Group%20headquarters%20in%20NYC%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6634e3c610dfcda409665f4e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EInvestors%20in%20Blackstone's%20real-estate%20fund%20asked%20for%20their%20money%20back%20in%20droves%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0more%20than%20%2415%20billion%20to%20date.%3Cp%3EJeenah%20Moon%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20rosy%20picture%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblackstones-data-center-bets-have-climbed-10-fold-to-100-billion-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBlackstone%20paints%3C%2Fa%3E%20may%20not%20tell%20the%20whole%20story.%20In%20recent%20months%20I've%20spoken%20with%20veteran%20analysts%2C%20accountants%2C%20and%20investors%20who%20have%20come%20to%20believe%20that%20BREIT%20is%20essentially%20a%20house%20of%20cards.%20That's%20because%20the%20returns%20the%20fund%20claims%20it%20has%20delivered%20depend%20almost%20entirely%20on%20BREIT's%20own%20estimates%2C%20which%20skeptics%20believe%20are%20wildly%20inflated.%20What's%20more%2C%20when%20BREIT%20faced%20a%20flood%20of%20redemption%20requests%20from%20investors%2C%20it%20only%20fulfilled%20all%20those%20requests%20after%20raising%20cash%20from%20new%20investors%20%E2%80%94%20including%20one%20that%20received%20a%20sweetheart%20deal%20from%20Blackstone%20to%20invest%20in%20BREIT.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20the%20absolute%20definition%20of%20a%20Ponzi%20scheme%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Nate%20Koppikar%2C%20who%20runs%20a%20hedge%20fund%20called%20Orso%20Partners%20that%20has%20shorted%20Blackstone's%20stock%20because%20of%20concerns%20over%20BREIT.%20Unless%20the%20real-estate%20market%20comes%20roaring%20back%2C%20analysts%20warn%2C%20BREIT%20could%20end%20up%20shrinking%20to%20a%20fraction%20of%20its%20current%20size%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eleaving%20the%20fund's%20investors%20holding%20the%20bag.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSurveying%20some%20of%20the%20ways%20that%20Blackstone%20has%20misled%20investors%20over%20the%20past%20five%20months%2C%20we%20are%20more%20convinced%20than%20ever%20that%20BREIT%20is%20a%20bad%20investment%20created%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20Blackstone%2C%26quot%3B%20Craig%20McCann%2C%20a%20financial%20analyst%20who%20served%20as%20an%20economist%20at%20the%20Securities%20Exchange%20Commission%2C%20wrote%20last%20year.%20%26quot%3BInvestors%20should%20not%20accept%20anything%20Blackstone%20and%20BREIT%20state%20as%20truthful.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20impossible%20to%20know%20exactly%20how%20valuable%20BREIT%20is.%20Because%20the%20fund%20is%20not%20publicly%20traded%2C%20the%20market%20doesn't%20set%20its%20price%20per%20share%20%E2%80%94%20Blackstone%20does.%20You%20buy%20shares%20in%20BREIT%20based%20on%20your%20faith%20in%20Blackstone's%20investing%20brilliance%20and%20in%20the%20firm's%20account%20of%20its%20own%20performance.%20Investing%20in%20a%20private%20real-estate%20trust%20like%20BREIT%20is%2C%20ultimately%2C%20an%20exercise%20in%20trust.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBREIT's%20returns%20are%20based%20on%20a%20measure%20called%20net%20asset%20value%2C%20or%20NAV.%20That's%20supposed%20to%20be%20the%20value%20of%20all%20the%20assets%20the%20fund%20owns%2C%20minus%20its%20debt.%20Blackstone%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20it%20has%20an%20%26quot%3Bincredibly%20rigorous%20valuation%20process%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0one%20it%20says%20has%20led%20it%20to%20adjust%20its%20NAV%20more%20aggressively%20than%20other%20REITS.%20But%20BREIT%20doesn't%20let%20investors%20or%20regulators%20see%20some%20of%20the%20crucial%20assumptions%20that%20go%20into%20calculating%20its%20NAV.%20As%20BREIT's%20financial%20documents%20state%2C%20Blackstone%20%26quot%3Bis%20ultimately%20and%20solely%20responsible%20for%20the%20determination%20of%20our%20NAV.%26quot%3B%20The%20methods%20used%20to%20calculate%20it%20are%20%26quot%3Bnot%20prescribed%20by%20rules%20of%20the%20SEC%20or%20any%20other%20regulatory%20agency%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20NAV%20%26quot%3Bis%20not%20audited%20by%20our%20independent%20registered%20public%20accounting%20firm.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChilton%20Capital%20Management%2C%20which%20invests%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-a-reit%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublicly%20traded%20REITs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20analyzed%20the%20way%20Blackstone%20adjusts%20the%20value%20of%20BREIT%20to%20reflect%20changes%20in%20the%20underlying%20real%20estate%20it%20owns.%20Rather%20than%20being%20%26quot%3Bmarked%20to%20market%26quot%3B%20every%20day%20%E2%80%94%20or%20every%20millisecond%2C%20like%20public%20REITS%20%E2%80%94%20Blackstone%20adjusts%20its%20NAV%20on%20a%20monthly%20basis.%20In%20today's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-mistake-buyers-sellers-mortgage-rates-time-to-buy-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evolatile%20real-estate%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20that%20means%20its%20stated%20value%20can%20lag%20way%20behind%20reality.%20%26quot%3BIt%20inherently%20is%20a%20flawed%20process%20when%20prices%20are%20changing%20quickly%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fchiltoncapital.com%2F2023%2F04%2F01%2Farbitrage-opportunity-available-in-public-reits-april-2023%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChilton%3C%2Fa%3E%20observes.%20%26quot%3BWe%20refer%20to%20this%20imperfect%20appraisal%20process%20as%20'mark%20to%20magic.'%26quot%3B%20In%202022%2C%20after%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-work-gutted-city-downtowns-office-real-estate-apocalypse-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecrash%20in%20commercial%20real%20estate%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20publicly%20traded%20REITs%20that%20own%20assets%20similar%20to%20BREIT's%20%E2%80%94%20multifamily%20housing%20and%20industrial%20buildings%20%E2%80%94%20have%20been%20selling%20at%20sharp%20discounts.%20But%20BREIT%2C%20by%20%26quot%3Bmarking%20to%20magic%2C%26quot%3B%20has%20continued%20to%20claim%20far%20higher%20returns.%20Using%20a%20collection%20of%20market-based%20metrics%2C%20Chilton%20concluded%20last%20April%20that%20BREIT%20was%20overstating%20the%20value%20of%20its%20NAV%20by%20more%20than%2055%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcCann%2C%20who%20is%20now%20a%20principal%20at%20SLCG%20Economics%20Consulting%2C%20reached%20a%20similar%20conclusion.%20He%20calculated%20that%20the%20cumulative%20returns%20of%20other%20funds%20in%20the%20sectors%20in%20which%20BREIT%20is%20concentrated%20plunged%20by%20over%2030%25%20in%202022.%20Yet%20BREIT%20claimed%20that%20its%20value%3Cem%3E%20increased%20%3C%2Fem%3Eduring%20the%20same%20period.%20In%20the%20dry%20language%20of%20market%20analysts%2C%20McCann%20called%20the%20fund's%20claims%20about%20its%20NAV%20%26quot%3Bunreliable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBlackstone%20considers%20such%20comparisons%20unfair.%20It%20insists%20that%20BREIT%20shouldn't%20be%20compared%20to%20publicly%20traded%20funds%2C%20which%20it%20argues%20are%20more%20volatile%20than%20private%20offerings.%20In%20a%20statement%20to%20BI%2C%20the%20firm%20insists%20that%20BREIT%20is%20able%20to%20outperform%20other%20funds%20for%20a%20simple%20reason%3A%20because%20it%20owns%20better%20assets%20than%20they%20do.%20BREIT's%20portfolio%2C%20Blackstone%20says%2C%20is%20%26quot%3Bconcentrated%20in%20the%20best%20performing%20sectors%20(data%20centers%2C%20logistics%20and%20student%20housing)%20and%20geographies%20(virtually%20no%20urban%20exposure).%26quot%3B%20Only%203%25%20of%20BREIT's%20holdings%20are%20in%20office%20buildings%2C%20which%20have%20been%20ground%20zero%20for%20commercial%20real%20estate%20pain.%20The%20company%20points%20to%20its%20performance%20during%20the%20global%20financial%20crisis%20of%202008%20as%20evidence%20of%20its%20ability%20to%20outperform%20its%20competitors%20during%20%26quot%3Bperiods%20of%20dislocation%26quot%3B%20and%20notes%20that%20it%20has%20sold%20%2420%20billion%20of%20real%20estate%20since%20the%20beginning%20of%202022%2C%20when%20interest%20rates%20began%20to%20rise%2C%20generating%20a%20profit%20of%20%244%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNot%20all%20real%20estate%20is%20created%20equal%2C%26quot%3B%20BREIT%20boasted%20in%20a%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.globest.com%2F2024%2F01%2F03%2Fblackstone-redemption-requests-drop-41-in-december%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eletter%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20stockholders%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20where%20you%20invest%20matters.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224724%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Shoppers%20seen%20outside%20Forum%20Sintra%2C%20one%20of%20four%20commercial%20centers%20owned%20by%20The%20Blackstone%20Group%20in%20Lisbon%20region%20in%20Sintra%2C%20Portugal.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6634e4a810dfcda409666035%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223020%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOne%20of%20four%20commercial%20centers%20Blackstone%20owns%20near%20Lisbon.%20The%20company%20argues%20that%20BREIT's%20valuation%20remains%20high%20because%20the%20assets%20in%20its%20portfolio%20are%20superior%20to%20those%20in%20other%20funds.%20%3Cp%3EHoracio%20Villalobos%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Blackstone's%20principal%20claim%20%E2%80%94%20that%20sounder%20investments%20have%20led%20to%20higher%20returns%20%E2%80%94%20is%20difficult%20to%20square%20with%20the%20ongoing%20decline%20of%20commercial%20real%20estate.%20It's%20hard%20to%20fathom%20how%20BREIT%20could%20have%20bought%20so%20many%20properties%20at%20the%20height%20of%20the%20market%20and%20yet%20somehow%20been%20selective%20enough%20to%20have%20dodged%20all%20the%20post-pandemic%20downturns%20suffered%20by%20other%20funds.%20According%20to%20BREIT's%20own%20numbers%2C%20data%20centers%20and%20student%20housing%20make%20up%20only%20a%20small%20part%20of%20its%20portfolio.%20And%20many%20of%20the%20data%20centers%20Blackstone%20says%20have%20already%20created%20so%20much%20value%20for%20the%20fund%20aren't%20even%20up%20and%20running%20yet%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20still%20in%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPublicly%20traded%20REITs%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20aren't%20the%20only%20ones%20marking%20down%20their%20assets.%20Bluerock%20Total%20Income%20%2B%20Real%20Estate%2C%20which%20has%20over%20%24300%20billion%20invested%20in%20a%20host%20of%20institutional%20real%20estate%20funds%2C%20has%20marked%20its%20NAV%20back%20to%20pre-pandemic%20levels%20%E2%80%94%20down%20more%20than%2020%25%20from%20its%20peak.%20Other%20major%20investors%2C%20unlike%20Blackstone%2C%20apparently%20don't%20see%20their%20real%20estate%20holdings%20as%20immune%20from%20the%20chaos%20buffeting%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBlackstone%20also%20argues%20in%20its%20marketing%20material%20that%20BREIT%20is%20better%20positioned%20than%20other%20real-estate%20funds%20because%20its%20balance%20sheet%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.breit.com%2Fportfolio%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bsubstantially%20hedged%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20meaning%20it%20has%20fixed-rate%20debt%20and%20derivatives%20in%20place%20that%20protect%20against%20rising%20interest%20rates.%20That's%20true%20%E2%80%94%20for%20the%20moment.%20But%20BREIT's%20future%20cash%20flows%20are%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20very%20sensitive%20to%20interest%20rates.%20At%20the%20end%20of%20last%20year%2C%20BREIT%20had%20%2462%20billion%20of%20debt%20secured%20by%20its%20properties%2C%20and%20it%20paid%20an%20effective%20interest%20rate%20of%204.3%25%20that%20it%20locked%20in%20before%20rates%20spiked.%20But%20%2447%20billion%20of%20that%20debt%20will%20come%20due%20over%20the%20next%20four%20years%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20if%20rates%20stay%20elevated%2C%20BREIT%20could%20face%20over%20%241%20billion%20in%20added%20interest%20costs.%20That%2C%20BREIT%20has%20warned%20investors%2C%20%26quot%3Bcould%20reduce%20our%20cash%20flows%20and%20our%20ability%20to%20make%20distributions%20to%20you.%26quot%3B%20Investing%20in%20BREIT%20is%20essentially%20a%20bet%20that%20interest%20rates%20are%20going%20to%20fall%20%E2%80%94%20because%20if%20they%20don't%2C%20it%20could%20be%20ruinous.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20might%20argue%20that%20it%20ultimately%20doesn't%20matter%20if%20BREIT%20is%20overvaluing%20its%20NAV.%20As%20long%20as%20investors%20keep%20getting%20their%20hefty%20annual%20dividends%2C%20who%20cares%3F%20That's%20basically%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-fraud-trial-experts-offer-chillaxed-theory-of-asset-valuation-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20same%20argument%20that%20Donald%20Trump%20made%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20defending%20himself%20against%20charges%20of%20systematically%20overstating%20his%20assets%20%E2%80%94%20that%20everybody%20made%20money%2C%20so%20no%20one%20was%20defrauded.%20But%20miscalculating%20the%20value%20of%20a%20vehicle%20like%20BREIT%20inflates%20the%20fees%20investors%20pay%20for%20participating%20in%20the%20fund%20while%20simultaneously%20depriving%20them%20of%20the%20opportunity%20to%20accurately%20assess%20the%20risk%20they're%20taking.%20In%20addition%2C%20Blackstone%20is%20incentivized%20to%20overvalue%20its%20NAV%2C%20because%20that's%20the%20number%20it%20uses%20to%20calculate%20the%20management%20and%20performance%20fees%20that%20investors%20pay.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20text-book%20example%20of%20conflict%20of%20interests%2C%26quot%3B%20Robert%20Chang%2C%20the%20head%20of%20securities%20litigation%20at%20Fideres%2C%20a%20consulting%20firm%20that%20specializes%20in%20investigating%20corporate%20wrongdoing%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20piece%20about%20BREIT.%20Fideres%20calculates%20that%20since%20early%202022%2C%20the%20fund's%20NAV%20per%20share%20has%20remained%20relatively%20stable%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0while%20public%20REITs%20have%20lost%20more%20than%2030%25%20of%20their%20value.%20If%20BREIT's%20assets%20are%20indeed%20overvalued%2C%20Fideres%20estimates%2C%20investors%20may%20have%20overpaid%20management%20and%20performance%20fees%20to%20the%20tune%20of%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20alarm%20bells%20over%20BREIT%20go%20beyond%20whether%20Blackstone%20is%20overstating%20the%20fund's%20value.%20BREIT%20has%20said%20that%20through%20June%20of%20last%20year%2C%20100%25%20of%20its%20dividends%20were%20funded%20by%20cash%20flows%20from%20operations%20%E2%80%94%20the%20money%20produced%20by%20its%20real-estate%20assets.%20But%20that%20claim%20is%20more%20than%20a%20little%20misleading.%20In%20the%20measure%20of%20cash%20that%20BREIT%20highlights%2C%20it%20doesn't%20subtract%20the%20expenditures%20required%20to%20maintain%20its%20properties%2C%20which%20is%20standard%20for%20the%20industry.%20In%20its%20own%20fine%20print%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20BREIT%20does%20provide%20several%20other%20measures%20that%20are%20more%20analogous%20to%20how%20most%20REITS%20define%20cash%20flow%3B%20by%20those%20measures%2C%20the%20fund%20has%20never%20been%20able%20to%20cover%20its%20dividend%20from%20its%20cash%20flow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20response%20to%20BI%2C%20Blackstone%20argues%20that%20because%20its%20management%20fees%20are%20not%20paid%20in%20cash%2C%20they%20are%20%26quot%3Bproperly%20excluded%26quot%3B%20from%20some%20of%20its%20measures.%20But%20not%20being%20able%20to%20pay%20the%20dividend%20you've%20promised%20can%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20Ponzi-ish%20warning%2C%20because%20it%20means%20the%20money%20has%20to%20come%20from%20selling%20off%20assets%2C%20borrowing%20money%2C%20or%20attracting%20new%20investors%20%E2%80%94%20a%20reality%20that%20BREIT%20acknowledges%20on%20the%20third%20page%20of%20its%20financial%20documents%20(and%20one%20that%20the%20SEC%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sec.gov%2Fresources-investors%2Finvestor-alerts-bulletins%2Fnon-traded-reits%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enoted%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20risk%20factor%20for%20all%20private%20REITS).%20And%20if%20you%20subtract%20Blackstone's%20fees%2C%20BREIT%20has%20covered%20less%20than%2050%25%20of%20its%20dividend%20distribution%20since%20its%20inception.%20Indeed%2C%20one%20of%20the%20primary%20reasons%20BREIT%20has%20been%20able%20to%20pay%20its%20dividends%20is%20because%20roughly%20half%20of%20all%20shareholders%20have%20elected%20to%20receive%20their%20dividends%20not%20in%20cash%2C%20but%20in%20more%20shares%20of%20BREIT.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20the%20game%20depends%20on%20the%20continued%20belief%20of%20investors%20%E2%80%94%20on%20their%20willingness%20to%20accept%20shares%20of%20BREIT%20in%20lieu%20of%20cash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20paid%20in%20shares%2C%20of%20course%2C%20is%20not%20the%20same%20as%20getting%20paid%20in%20cash.%20The%20more%20shares%20BREIT%20issues%20to%20pay%20the%20dividend%20%E2%80%94%20and%20its%20fees%20to%20Blackstone%20%E2%80%94%20the%20less%20each%20share%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eis%20worth.%20%26quot%3BOn%20the%20surface%2C%20it%20all%20looks%20so%20safe%2C%26quot%3B%20McCann%20tells%20BI.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20getting%204%25%20or%20so%20a%20year%2C%20and%20you%20think%20it%20looks%20like%20a%20bond%2C%20and%20you%20think%20the%20underlying%20investments%20are%20doing%20well.%20Only%20when%20you%20dig%20in%20do%20you%20figure%20out%20that%20even%20if%20you're%20taking%20cash%2C%20the%20money%20is%20a%20return%20%3Cem%3Eof%3C%2Fem%3E%20capital%2C%20not%20a%20return%20%3Cem%3Eon%3C%2Fem%3E%20capital.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20when%20investors%20started%20asking%20for%20their%20money%20back%20in%20droves%2C%20BREIT%20faced%20a%20big%20problem.%20If%20its%20assets%20weren't%20marked%20correctly%2C%20it%20couldn't%20sell%20them%20off%20to%20pay%20investors%20without%20fessing%20up.%20Then%20the%20fund%20got%20what%20looked%20like%20a%20vote%20of%20confidence.%20In%20January%202023%2C%20BREIT%20announced%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funiversity-of-california-invests-4-billion-with-blackstone-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUniversity%20of%20California%20had%20decided%20to%20invest%20%244%20billion%20in%20the%20fund%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20giving%20it%20a%20much-needed%20infusion%20of%20cash.%20Schwarzman%20called%20the%20investment%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.breit.com%2Fpress-releases%2Farticle%2Fuc-investments-creates-strategic-venture-with-blackstone-to-invest-4-billion-in-breit-common-shares%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bvalidation%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20BREIT's%20strategy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20wasn't.%20To%20entice%20the%20university%20to%20invest%2C%20Blackstone%20had%20offered%20it%20a%20special%20deal.%20BREIT%20agreed%20to%20award%20the%20university%20an%20additional%20%241%20billion%20in%20stock%20in%20the%20event%20that%20the%20fund's%20rate%20of%20return%20fell%20below%2011.25%25.%20The%20deal%20was%20so%20sweet%20that%20UC's%20Board%20of%20Regents%20quickly%20agreed%20to%20invest%20another%20%24500%20million%20on%20the%20same%20terms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BContrary%20to%20Blackstone's%20spin%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20McCann%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20University%20of%20California%20investment%20strongly%20supports%20the%20view%20that%20BREIT%20is%20a%20terrible%20investment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224805%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20sign%20is%20placed%20in%20the%20hallways%20outside%20of%20the%20Chancellors%20office%20during%20a%20protest%20calling%20for%20the%20UC%20Retirement%20Plan%20to%20divest%20from%20Blackstone%20at%20UCLA%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20Feb.%2014%2C%202024%20in%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20CA.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6634f544ec0c69656900b88c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223203%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EStudents%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%20protested%20the%20school%20system's%20investment%20in%20BREIT%2C%20which%20came%20after%20Blackstone%20offered%20a%20special%20guarantee%20on%20the%20deal.%3Cp%3EMichael%20Blackshire%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EScoring%20the%20new%20investment%20helped%20BREIT%20pay%20off%20all%20those%20who%20wanted%20to%20exit%20the%20fund%2C%20albeit%20slowly.%20And%20for%20the%20moment%2C%20the%20stampede%20appears%20to%20have%20subsided.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBlackstone%20says%20that%20BREIT%20has%20%26quot%3Baccess%20to%20ample%20liquidity%20across%20multiple%20sources%2C%26quot%3B%20including%20%26quot%3B%24119.1%20billion%20of%20high-quality%20real%20estate%20that%20can%20be%20sold%20at%20market%20prices%20if%20we%20choose%20to%20do%20so.%26quot%3B%20But%20if%20investors%20stage%20another%20rush%20for%20the%20doors%2C%20BREIT%20could%20face%20a%20serious%20reckoning%2C%20especially%20given%20its%20high%20level%20of%20debt.%20If%20it%20has%20overvalued%20its%20properties%2C%20as%20some%20experts%20suggest%2C%20then%20it%20will%20have%20to%20sell%20its%20assets%20at%20a%20price%20below%20where%20they%20are%20marked.%20And%20the%20more%20shareholders%20it%20has%20to%20redeem%2C%20the%20faster%20its%20equity%20will%20become%20worthless.%20Those%20who%20get%20their%20money%20out%20early%20will%20be%20OK.%20Those%20who%20are%20last%20in%20line%2C%20not%20so%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20BREIT%20has%20to%20sell%20properties%20to%20meet%20redemptions%2C%20and%20they%20have%20to%20dip%20deeper%20into%20their%20portfolio%20to%20sell%20less%20desirable%20properties%2C%20they'll%20have%20to%20mark%20their%20NAV%20to%20reflect%20the%20actual%20sales%20prices%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Phil%20Bak%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Armada%20Investors%2C%20a%20quantitative%20asset%20manager%20that%20specializes%20in%20REITs.%20%26quot%3BThat%20could%20scare%20the%20people%20who%20have%20been%20clinging%20to%20fund%20performance%20as%20a%20reason%20not%20to%20redeem%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20causes%20a%20death%20spiral.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20one%20I%20spoke%20with%20believes%20that%20Blackstone%20set%20out%20to%20build%20a%20house%20of%20cards.%20Rather%2C%20they%20say%2C%20BREIT%20was%20a%20victim%20of%20its%20own%20success.%20Money%20poured%20in%20at%20the%20height%20of%20the%20market%2C%20meaning%20that%20BREIT%20invested%20at%20a%20moment%20when%20commercial%20real%20estate%20was%20priced%20to%20perfection.%20Real%20estate%2C%20by%20its%20nature%2C%20is%20always%20somewhat%20illiquid%20%E2%80%94%20you%20can't%20sell%20your%20share%20of%20an%20apartment%20building%20on%20the%20stock%20market.%20And%20in%20a%20bad%20market%2C%20it's%20%3Cem%3Every%3C%2Fem%3E%20illiquid%2C%20especially%20if%20what%20you%20own%20is%20marked%20at%20a%20price%20where%20no%20one%20will%20buy%20it.%20But%20while%20Blackstone%20says%20it%20designed%20BREIT%20so%20investors%20could%20get%20their%20money%20out%2C%20it%20seems%20not%20to%20have%20foreseen%20that%20scores%20of%20individual%20investors%20%E2%80%94%20unlike%20the%20big%20institutions%20that%20have%20typically%20been%20its%20clients%2C%20who%20are%20forced%20to%20commit%20their%20funds%20for%20long%20periods%20of%20time%20%E2%80%94%20might%20get%20spooked%20enough%20to%20ask%20for%20their%20money%20back%20all%20at%20the%20same%20time.%20Titans%20of%20Wall%20Street%20often%20believe%20that%20their%20brilliance%20should%20insulate%20them%20from%20skepticism.%20Their%20supreme%20confidence%20in%20their%20own%20wisdom%20is%20perhaps%20their%20most%20marketable%20asset.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20completely%20possible%2C%20of%20course%2C%20that%20BREIT%20will%20survive%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20flawed%20its%20model%20might%20be.%20If%20the%20real-estate%20market%20reignites%2C%20that%20will%20boost%20the%20value%20of%20the%20assets%20in%20funds%20like%20BREIT.%20And%20if%20enough%20new%20investors%20are%20willing%20to%20place%20bets%20on%20BREIT%20%E2%80%94%20if%20trust%20in%20Blackstone's%20%26quot%3Bmagic%26quot%3B%20remains%20high%20%E2%80%94%20then%20everyone%20will%20keep%20making%20money%2C%20if%20only%20on%20paper%2C%20even%20if%20BREIT%20is%20overvaluing%20its%20assets.%20Blackstone's%20success%20has%20already%20created%20at%20least%20three%20billionaires%2C%20chief%20among%20them%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsteve-schwarzmans-life-2015-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECEO%2C%20Steve%20Schwarzman%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20is%20worth%20almost%20%2440%20billion.%20The%20ability%20to%20enrich%20yourself%20seems%20to%20be%20a%20key%20part%20of%20what%20inspires%20others%20to%20follow%20your%20investment%20advice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Stephen%20A.%20Schwarzman%2C%20Chairman%20and%20CEO%20of%20the%20Blackstone%20Group%2C%20listens%20to%20discussions%20at%20the%20Bloomberg%20Global%20Business%20forum%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6634e370ec0c69656900a9a0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECEO%20Stephen%20Schwarzman%20insists%20the%20worst%20is%20behind%20Blackstone%2C%20even%20as%20analysts%20remain%20worried%20about%20BREIT's%20prospects%20in%20a%20volatile%20market.%3Cp%3EShannon%20Stapleton%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20are%20plenty%20of%20warning%20signs%20that%20things%20could%20get%20worse.%20It's%20unlikely%20that%20the%20market%20will%20pick%20up%20fast%20enough%20to%20offset%20BREIT's%20woes.%20%26quot%3BCommercial%20real%20estate%20is%20a%20slow%20burn%2C%26quot%3B%20Brian%20Moynihan%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Bank%20of%20America%2C%20recently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2024-03-19%2Fbofa-s-moynihan-says-commercial-real-estate-will-be-slow-burn%3Fsref%3D6y0OF8u2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eobserved%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20its%20financial%20statements%2C%20Blackstone%20says%20it%20continues%20to%20count%20on%20%26quot%3Bhigh%20single-digit%20growth%26quot%3B%20in%20its%20two%20biggest%20sectors%2C%20rental%20housing%20and%20industrial%20properties.%20But%20BREIT's%20overall%20growth%20was%20just%206%25%20last%20year%2C%20and%20it%20has%20been%20decelerating%20quarter%20over%20quarter.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIf%20the%20market%20continues%20to%20fall%2C%20it%20will%20be%20harder%20for%20BREIT%20to%20claim%20it's%20the%20shining%20exception%3Cstrong%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20make%20matters%20worse%2C%20the%20way%20BREIT%20is%20structured%20could%20prove%20to%20be%20a%20ticking%20time%20bomb.%20Like%20other%20private%20vehicles%2C%20BREIT%20pays%20hefty%20commissions%20to%20financial%20advisors%20who%20steer%20their%20clients%20to%20the%20fund.%20All%20told%2C%20Blackstone%20has%20paid%20Wall%20Street%20banks%20and%20brokers%20more%20than%20%24700%20million%20in%20brokerage%20fees.%20But%20for%20brokers%20who%20put%20their%20clients%20in%20BREIT%20early%20on%2C%20those%20commissions%20could%20soon%20hit%20a%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dlapiper.com%2Fen-us%2Finsights%2Fpublications%2F2022%2F05%2Ffrequently-asked-questions-about-nav-reits%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20mandated%20%3C%2Fa%3Ecap%20of%208.75%25%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20they'll%20no%20longer%20be%20incentivized%20to%20sell%20the%20fund.%20If%20they%20start%20advising%20their%20clients%20to%20exit%20BREIT%2C%20it%20could%20spur%20an%20even%20bigger%20rush%20for%20the%20doors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20future%20of%20BREIT%20could%20also%20send%20shock%20waves%20through%20Blackstone's%20bottom%20line.%20In%202022%20alone%2C%20SLCG%20calculated%2C%20fees%20from%20BREIT%20generated%2013.3%25%20of%20Blackstone's%20total%20management%20fees%20and%2012.6%25%20of%20its%20performance%20revenue.%20If%20BREIT%20and%20its%20sister%20fund%2C%20BPP%2C%20are%20forced%20to%20slash%20their%20NAVs%20by%2050%25%2C%20the%20ensuing%20reduction%20in%20fees%20would%20wipe%20out%20over%2015%25%20of%20Blackstone's%20fee-related%20earnings%20%E2%80%94%20earnings%20that%20Wall%20Street%2C%20in%20contrast%2C%20is%20expecting%20will%20%3Cem%3Egrow%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%2015%25.%20According%20to%20Blackstone's%20financial%20statements%2C%20it's%20already%20anticipating%20it%20will%20have%20to%20pay%20the%20University%20of%20California%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.theregistrysf.com%2Fbreits-reports-annual-loss-owing-university-of-california-560-million%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%24564%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20BREIT%20stock%20%E2%80%94%20an%20expense%20it%20doesn't%20count%20in%20the%20numbers%20it%20highlights%20to%20Wall%20Street.%20If%20BREIT%20craters%2C%20it%20will%20also%20be%20difficult%20for%20Blackstone%20to%20live%20up%20to%20Wall%20Street's%20expectations%20for%20its%20long-term%20earnings%20growth%2C%20which%20depend%20in%20part%20on%20its%20successful%20expansion%20into%20the%20retail%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20bigger%20issues%20at%20stake%20than%20Blackstone's%20bottom%20line.%20It's%20worth%20remembering%2C%20as%20Chilton%20notes%2C%20that%20private%20funds%20like%20BREIT%20were%20among%20%26quot%3Bthe%20biggest%20losers%26quot%3B%20during%20the%20global%20financial%20crisis%20of%202008.%20But%20that%20lesson%20seems%20lost%20on%20today's%20investors%2C%20who%20have%20once%20again%20flocked%20to%20private%20real-estate%20funds%20in%20a%20time%20of%20extreme%20market%20volatility.%20In%20the%20two%20years%20after%20the%20pandemic%20hit%2C%20private%20funds%20like%20BREIT%20raised%20%2467%20billion%20%E2%80%94%20far%20more%20than%20they%20drummed%20up%20in%20the%20two%20years%20leading%20up%20to%20the%20Great%20Recession.%20%26quot%3BWhile%20the%20tombstones%20may%20have%20different%20names%20on%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Chilton%20observes%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20reasons%20for%20the%20demise%20of%20private%20equity%20real%20estate%20players%20are%20going%20to%20rhyme%2C%20and%20possibly%20mirror%20those%20from%20the%20global%20financial%20crisis.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20the%20story%20of%20BREIT%20involves%20more%20than%20profits%20and%20losses.%20It's%20only%20recently%20that%20private-equity%20firms%20like%20Blackstone%20have%20started%20offering%20products%20to%20ordinary%20investors.%20%26quot%3BBREIT%20was%20a%20test%20case%20for%20the%20whole%20industry%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Koppikar%2C%20of%20Orso%20Partners.%20Perhaps%2C%20given%20the%20questions%20swirling%20around%20BREIT%2C%20it's%20time%20to%20rethink%20whether%20the%20world's%20wealthiest%20funds%20should%20be%20trusted%20to%20take%20billions%20of%20dollars%20in%20fees%20from%20ordinary%20investors%20without%20more%20oversight.%20As%20it%20stands%2C%20it's%20impossible%20to%20know%20what%20BREIT's%20assets%20are%20actually%20worth%20%E2%80%94%20and%20therein%20lies%20the%20problem.%20In%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20market%20price%2C%20independent%20accounting%20and%20tighter%20government%20regulation%20are%20needed%20to%20ensure%20that%20investors%20have%20the%20accurate%2C%20verifiable%20numbers%20they%20need%20to%20make%20informed%20decisions.%20With%20private%20funds%20like%20BREIT%2C%20too%20much%20maneuvering%20takes%20place%20in%20the%20dark.%20And%20if%20history%20is%20any%20lesson%2C%20the%20dark%20is%20a%20very%20bad%20place%20to%20be%20doing%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fbethany-mc-lean%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EBethany%20McLean%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20special%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%