%20them%20with%20the%20Gold%20Star%20medal%20on%20the%20eve%20of%20the%20%26quot%3BHeroes%20of%20the%20Fatherland%20Day%26quot%3B%20at%20the%20Kremlin%20in%20Moscow%20on%20December%208%2C%202022.%3Cp%3EMikhail%20Metzel%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ERussia%20has%20a%20manpower%20crunch%20because%20of%20its%20war%20with%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERussia's%20military%20is%20paying%20more%20in%20sign-on%20bonuses%20and%20salaries%20than%20the%20oil%20and%20gas%20sector.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERussia's%20oil%20and%20gas%20revenues%20have%20been%20keeping%20its%20war%20chest%20filled.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20is%20facing%20a%20labor%20crisis%20as%20its%20war%20with%20Ukraine%20siphons%20manpower%20away%20from%20the%20country's%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20manpower%20crunch%20has%20gotten%20so%20bad%20that%20the%20Russian%20military%20is%20now%20offering%20sign-on%20bonuses%20and%20salaries%20that%20are%20so%20competitive%20that%20even%20the%20country's%20lucrative%20oil%20and%20gas%20industry%20isn't%20keeping%20up%2C%20Bloomberg%20reported%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia's%20oil%20and%20gas%20sector%20has%20been%20paying%20wages%20that%20are%20at%20least%20two-thirds%20higher%20than%20the%20national%20average%20wage%20since%202017%2C%20per%20Bloomberg%20calculations%20based%20on%20official%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20no%20longer%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20January%20and%20February%2C%20workers%20in%20Russia's%20oil%20and%20gas%20sector%20took%20home%20about%20125%2C200%20rubles%2C%20or%20%241%2C370%2C%20in%20monthly%20nominal%20salary%2C%20per%20the%20media%20outlet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Russian%20army%20is%20now%20offering%20incentives%20to%20contract%20soldiers%2C%20including%20a%20nationwide%20sign-on%20bonus%20of%20195%2C000%20rubles%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcontract.gosuslugi.ru%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERussian%20government%20portal.