matic%20distortions%20in%20space-time.%20The%20surrounding%20accretion%20disk%20--%20a%20swirling%20mass%20of%20hot%20gas%20--%20and%20background%20stars%20appear%20significantly%20warped%2C%20like%20looking%20at%20a%20funhouse%20mirror.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20camera%20gets%20closer%2C%20the%20light%20from%20stars%20and%20the%20swirling%20disk%20of%20gas%20around%20the%20black%20hole%20looks%20brighter%20and%20brighter%2C%20like%20the%20roar%20of%20a%20race%20car%20getting%20louder%20as%20it%20speeds%20by.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FdGEIsnBRWGs%3Fsi%3DAqfpVVbdjPKK8fKI%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22650%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20takes%20about%203%20hours%20for%20the%20camera%20to%20get%20to%20the%20event%20horizon%2C%20but%C2%A0to%20someone%20watching%20from%20far%20away%2C%C2%A0it%20seems%20like%20the%20camera%20never%20quite%20reaches%20it.%C2%A0The%20closer%20it%20gets%2C%20the%20slower%20it%20appears%20to%20move%20until%20it%20looks%20like%20it%20has%20stopped%20altogether.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20simulation%2C%20there%20are%20two%20possible%20outcomes%20for%C2%A0NASA's%C2%A0camera.%C2%A0In%20one%20scenario%2C%20it%20narrowly%20misses%20the%20event%20horizon%2C%20while%C2%A0in%20the%20other%2C%C2%A0it%20crosses%20over%20this%20boundary.%C2%A0If%20the%20camera%20crosses%20this%20line%2C%20it%20goes%20through%20a%20dramatic%20process%20called%C2%A0%26quot%3Bspaghettification%26quot%3B%2C%C2%A0%3Cwbr%3Ewhich%20means%20the%20intense%20gravitational%20forces%20near%20the%20black%20hole%20will%20pull%20on%20the%20camera%20so%C2%A0strongly%C2%A0that%20it%20will%20get%20stretched%20and%20torn%20apart%20within%2012.8%20seconds.%C2%A0This%C2%A0happens%20as%20it%20speeds%20towards%20the%20black%C2%A0hole's%C2%A0core%2C%20where%20there%20is%20a%20point%20of%20unimaginable%20density%20called%20the%C2%A0%E2%80%9Csingularity%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20in%20an%20alternative%20scenario%20where%20the%20camera%20orbits%20close%20to%20the%20event%20horizon%20but%20does%20not%20cross%20it%2C%20time%20will%20start%20acting%20strangely.%20It%20will%20stretch%20or%20dilate.%20For%20the%20astronaut%20on%20the%20camera%2C%20time%20ticks%20away%20as%20usual.%20But%20for%20those%20watching%20from%20far%20away%2C%20time%20appears%20to%20slow%20down.%20This%20time-dilation%20effect%20means%20that%20when%20the%20astronaut%20returns%2C%20they%20will%20actually%20be%20younger%20than%20their%20colleagues%20who%20stayed%20far%20from%20the%20black%20hole.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715065860000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2Fvascmlt8_black-hole-visualisation_625x300_07_May_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fnasas-latest-simulation-allows-us-to-see-whats-inside-black-holes-5607017%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22This%20simulation%20will%20help%20us%20dive%20into%20the%20event%20horizon%2C%20the%20boundary%20beyond%20which%20nothing%2C%20not%20even%20light%2C%20can%20escape.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fnasas-latest-simulation-allows-us-to-see-whats-inside-black-holes-5607017%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fnasas-latest-simulation-allows-us-to-see-whats-inside-black-holes-5607017%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fnasas-latest-simulation-allows-us-to-see-whats-inside-black-holes-5607017%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Visa%20appoints%20Sujai%20Raina%20as%20India%20head%3B%20to%20oversee%20strategic%20initiatives%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715065815000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.busi